<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=simba256&buddyTimeStamp=20070426&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.millsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1177908083&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Simba</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>This girl loves to dance while listening to reggae, rap, and R&B. In her Westridge home at <a href='/home/?user=simba256'>20057 Eagle Circle</a>, her neighbors can always tell if she's around by whether or not there's music pumping from her stereo. <br><br>A citizen since March 1, 2005, Simba is a confident girl who is a great problem solver. She finds games and crossword puzzles to be extremely challenging and fun! And when it comes to team sports, she's got a competitive streak that's contagious. On the basketball court or at the ice rink, she'll get you fired up! Just one look at her trophy collection will show you how involved she is.<br><br>This spring, she's looking forward to spending more time outdoors, and adding more cool furniture to her yard. Her substantial home has room for her to both work and play. She uses her martial arts studio to seriously practice what she learns at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/communitycenter/dojo/">dojo</a>. She designed cozy, bright-colored bedrooms for pillow fighting and game playing. She has plenty of yard space for athletic training or just goofing off. Simba understands the need for balance, and the way she designed her home reflects that.<br><br>So, stop by Simba's house and learn more about her. Listen out for her music and you'll know whether she's home! <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Simba, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week! </div>
